Safeguarding is everybody's business and at Diabetes UK we play an active part
in keeping children and adults at risk, safe. This includes ensuring we act,
prevent harm and promote safety in all aspects of work, and take appropriate
steps if we have a worry about a child or adult at risk.
Our Safeguarding procedures for children and adults at risk (PDF, 1.9MB)
explain how we respond to concerns or worries in line with the law and best
Safety and wellbeing is always our priority and there may be occasions when we
need to share information about individuals with other agencies in order to
* because there are concerns someone could be at risk of significant harm.
If you would like any more information you can contact the safeguarding team
By post: Safeguarding Team, Diabetes UK, Wells Lawrence House, 126 Back Church
